	"notes": [
		{
			"id": "nFVlasj9i7J4SSTy5",
			"markdown": "Soldiers are trained fighters, disciplined enforcers, hardened mercenaries, and professional warriors who survive violence through skill, courage, and relentless conditioning. Some are loyal patriots defending a nation or cause; others are corporate security contractors, pirate raiders, rebel fighters, gang enforcers, or wandering mercenaries selling their talents to the highest bidder. In a cyberpunk city they might serve as militarized police, tactical response teams, or augmented street soldiers. In a space opera they may fight aboard warships, defend frontier colonies, or deploy onto alien worlds under fire. Whatever their allegiance, Soldiers are defined by training, aggression, and the ability to function under deadly pressure.\n\nA Soldier’s primary role is surviving and prevailing in violent conflict, but a good Soldier is far more than someone who can shoot straight. Many Soldiers also serve as scouts, vehicle crews, engineers, commanders, security specialists, bodyguards, peacekeepers, or survival experts, developing expertise in tactics, reconnaissance, leadership, navigation, communications, demolitions, heavy weapons, or hostile-environment operations. Even away from the battlefield, you remain useful through discipline, situational awareness, intimidation, logistics, operational planning, and the ability to function calmly in chaotic or life-threatening situations. Whether you are a hardened infantry veteran, a disciplined officer, a mechanized cavalryman, a stealthy reconnaissance operative, or a power-armored assault trooper, the group depends on you whenever violence becomes unavoidable.\n\nSoldiers vary enormously depending on their training, battlefield role, and the needs of the campaign. Before selecting a package, make sure it fits the GM’s setting assumptions, available technology, and the intended style of play.\n\n*Armored Troopers* are tank crews, mechanized infantry, grav-vehicle operators, convoy escorts, cavalry equivalents, and walker pilots who dominate battlefields through mobility and overwhelming firepower. Whether operating tanks, mecha, armored cars, hovercraft, or gunships, Armored Troopers bring devastating force wherever they deploy. They emphasize Driving or Piloting, Gunner, Artillery, Navigation, Mechanic, and Forward Observer, backed by traits such as Combat Reflexes, Daredevil, Born Soldier, Born Tactician, High Pain Threshold, and Fearlessness. Their disadvantages frequently reflect the bravado and fatalism associated with mechanized warfare, including Overconfidence, Compulsive Gambling, Lecherousness, Trickster, Bad Temper, or Compulsive Carousing.\n\n*Battlesuit Troopers* are elite power-armored infantry trained to operate advanced combat exoskeletons, mechanized assault frames, or sealed tactical armor systems. Depending on the setting, Battlesuit Troopers may be elite commandos, corporate supersoldiers, knightly heavy infantry, or disposable mass-produced shock troops sealed inside walking tanks. Battlesuit Troopers excel at boarding actions, heavy assaults, hazardous-environment warfare, shock attacks, and fighting in conditions that would kill ordinary troops outright. They emphasize Battlesuit, Electronics Operation, Navigation, Mechanic, Gunner, and Forward Observer, supported by traits such as Combat Reflexes, High Pain Threshold, Fearlessness, Fit, and Born Soldier. The physical and psychological strain of operating advanced combat armor often contributes to disadvantages such as Overconfidence, Bloodlust, Berserk, Workaholic, Flashbacks, or Trickster.\n\n*Combat Engineers* are sappers, breachers, demolitions experts, military technicians, drone warfare specialists, and battlefield problem-solvers who keep armies functioning under impossible conditions. Some are meticulous professionals; others are reckless combat scientists who treat battlefields like engineering experiments. Combat Engineers excel at fortifications, sabotage, demolitions, field repairs, siege operations, drone support, and overcoming obstacles that brute force alone cannot solve. They emphasize Engineer (Combat), Explosives, Electronics Operation, Mathematics, Navigation, Gunner, and technical support skills, supported by traits such as Gizmo, Common Sense, Single-Minded, Intuition, and Born Tactician. Their disadvantages often stem from obsession, technical curiosity, or professional detachment, including Curious, Miserliness, Obsession, Workaholic, Truthfulness, or Callous.\n\n*Infantry* are line troops, marines, riot police, gang enforcers, mercenaries, and shock troopers who form the backbone of organized combat forces. Some become disciplined professionals devoted to protecting their comrades, while others harden into brutal killers shaped entirely by war. Infantry excel at direct combat, defensive operations, room-clearing, urban warfare, and holding territory under pressure. They emphasize Beam Weapons or Guns, Gunner, Survival, Urban Survival, Navigation, Hiking, and Forward Observer, supported by traits such as Combat Reflexes, Fearlessness, Fit, High Pain Threshold, and Born Soldier. Their disadvantages often reflect aggression, exhaustion, or battlefield conditioning, including Bad Temper, Bloodlust, Berserk, Bully, Callous, Overconfidence, or Sense of Duty.\n\n*Officers* are commanders, tacticians, military aristocrats, pirate captains, political officers, squad leaders, and warlords responsible for coordinating troops and making strategic decisions under pressure. A good Officer turns frightened, exhausted people into an organized fighting force; a bad one gets them killed. Officers excel at command, morale, logistics, planning, negotiation, and keeping soldiers functioning in the middle of chaos. They emphasize Leadership, Tactics, Administration, Diplomacy, Law (Military), Strategy, and Public Speaking, supported by traits such as Charisma, Born War-Leader, Born Tactician, Cultural Adaptability, Intuition, and Unfazeable. The burden of authority and ideology often creates disadvantages such as Sense of Duty, Honesty, Fanaticism, Jealousy, Selfless, or Code of Honor (Soldier’s).\n\n*Rangers* are scouts, reconnaissance troops, commandos, insurgents, resistance fighters, and wilderness patrol specialists who operate beyond conventional front lines. Rangers survive where maps fail, supply lines collapse, and ordinary troops refuse to go. Rangers excel at infiltration, ambushes, reconnaissance, long-range patrols, and independent operations far from support. They emphasize Camouflage, Stealth, Survival, Navigation, Electronics Operation, Hiking, and Forward Observer, often combined with Beam Weapons or Guns, supported by traits such as Absolute Direction, Danger Sense, Intuition, Night Vision, Rapid Healing, and Fearlessness. The isolation and stress of their profession often lead to disadvantages such as Loner, Nightmares, Flashbacks, Fanaticism, Stubbornness, Workaholic, or Xenophobia.\n\n*Space Troopers* are vacuum-trained soldiers specializing in orbital warfare, boarding operations, and combat in hostile extraterrestrial environments. Whether serving aboard naval warships, corporate security fleets, pirate raiders, or orbital marine corps, Space Troopers fight in places where a single mistake can kill everyone nearby. Space Troopers excel at boarding enemy vessels, defending stations and spacecraft, surviving hostile environments, and conducting military operations where atmosphere, gravity, and terrain cannot be trusted. They emphasize Free Fall, Spacer, Vacc Suit, Navigation, and survival skills needed for zero-gravity and deep-space deployment, supported by traits such as Absolute Direction, Danger Sense, Fearlessness, G-Experience, and Born Spacer. The isolation and psychological stress of space warfare often lead to disadvantages such as Flashbacks, Nightmares, Xenophobia, Workaholic, Loner, or Fanaticism."
		}
	]
}
